*And having some time to kill I headed to the 25 minute documentary, Alma, about the little known brother of Monterey’s very well-known Philharmonic, with music composed by his German chemist cousin, Heitor Almeida. I had some pre-conceived notions about the film (the most extreme being that it needed to be about a yearning Latino, mano-a-mano, with a zoomed in shot of those close-up jowels and drooping lids), but it was actually quite good.

Now it’s on to the airport, and if American Airlines and/or the waiting gate chair is reading this, I’m happy to lift off right now. Click!
